This chicken dish is very good, and probably does actually verge on "delicious." I skinned the thighs, but didn't bone them; next time I'd buy them already boned. I followed the recipe as written, but added three small garlic cloves to the browning chicken, removed them when lightly browned, and then put them back in the simmering sauce. At the end, they were soft and I mashed them into the sauce. I needed to use orange juice from frozen concentrate which is probably why my sauce wasn't overly sweet as it might have been if I had my very sweet oranges ready to pick from my tree. I feel the success of the sauce depends on patience in reducing it rather than thickening by any method. It really does thicken nicely in time.

