Rating: 3
Note that I'm just rating the sauce here; I only had bone-in (no skin, though) thighs, so I made the sauce separately in a pot (using Chinese chile sauce instead of Tabasco sauce, and a little extra chile sauce as well as brown sugar) and made sure to reduce it well. Then I browned the thighs well in a pan in a little olive oil, and brushed some of the sauce on both sides. I roasted the thighs in the oven at 450 until done, and after they were done cooked half a minced onion and a segmented orange (to continue the orange theme) in the juices in the roasting pan. I added the sauce, and served it over the roasted thighs. Personally I thought it was different, tasty, and easy. I will try it with the boneless meat at another point.

